1
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:11,067
Run!

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:15,267
Please help me!

3
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,700
Grandma!

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,800
King! King!

5
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:21,400
King, my grandson!

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,567
Are you waiting for Miss Lolita
 and her packed lunch?

7
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,767
Of course not.

8
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:30,200
You say that,
but don't you miss King?

9
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:32,700
Hello?

10
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,900
We're here at the lobby.

11
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,233
What?

12
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:38,400
Wait for me. Don't go anywhere.

13
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,767
Son, King's having
a hard time breathing.

14
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,600
I'll take him to the hospital.

15
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:44,600
I'll be there.

16
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:04,100
We're not leaving until we find
 a piece of evidence

17
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,167
that would lead us
to the kidnapper.

18
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:09,333
This one's interesting.

19
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:14,167
Policarpio, where are you?

20
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,300
I need you at the police station
 right now.

21
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:17,467
Yes, sir.

22
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,133
My son. Ma...

23
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:22,467
- Daddy!
- Ma.

24
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,833
Daddy!

25
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,467
Daddy... Daddy...

26
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:29,967
What he's experiencing right now
 is a massive panic attack.

27
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,700
We can sedate him
if you want.

28
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:33,600
Hi, King!

29
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,867
I know you're scared.
I can help you.

30
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,200
Here, let me show you a trick.

31
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:40,333
It's called box breathing.

32
00:01:43,733 --> 00:01:44,900
Thank you.

33
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:46,900
I was unsure of what to do.

34
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:48,367
So I'm glad you were there,

35
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:49,833
for my son.

36
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,367
I really appreciate that.

37
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:52,633
I mean it.

38
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:53,733
So, thank you.

39
00:01:55,267 --> 00:01:56,733
My ride is here.

40
00:01:58,367 --> 00:01:59,633
I'll see you around, alright?

41
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,733
Of course. Take care.

42
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:17,400
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:35,567 --> 00:02:39,533
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:41,700
It's locked.

45
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,567
[WOMAN] You're so stupid!

46
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,733
You're way too old
to be falling for scams!

47
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:47,933
Was I supposed to know that?

48
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,367
You should've used your head!

49
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:51,233
How could you have won
10 million pesos from a raffle

50
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:52,400
you didn't even join?

51
00:02:52,567 --> 00:02:53,900
Hey, Arissa!

52
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,633
Did you forget something?

53
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:56,733
Huh?

54
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,100
Where's your new place at?

55
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:01,067
I heard you're living
in a subdivision now.

56
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:02,300
We moved?

57
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:04,733
Yeah. Didn't you move with them?

58
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,900
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

59
00:03:07,067 --> 00:03:08,733
Let's go.
I'm not done with you yet!

60
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,100
Oh, I'm so mad right now!

61
00:03:10,267 --> 00:03:11,267
What a reckless man!

62
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:13,867
[ENZO]
Arissa, why don't we ask Mael?

63
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:16,233
- Come on.
- No need.

64
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,433
They weren't even looking
for me.

65
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:21,567
They're better off without me.

66
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:24,167
Come on, Arissa.

67
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,233
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

68
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,567
Coming here was a mistake, Enzo.

69
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:31,400
They already moved on.

70
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:50,667
King, my son...

71
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:54,400
If you ever feel scared again,

72
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,967
you can always come to me.

73
00:03:57,133 --> 00:03:58,300
To your grandma.

74
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,267
Or even to your teachers.

75
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:02,167
We'll always be there for you.

76
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,000
Okay, Daddy.

77
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:05,367
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

78
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:09,500
And always remember what
Miss Agnes taught you.

79
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:14,933
Daddy, please tell her that
I said thank you.

80
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:17,367
That she's a nice woman.

81
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:19,967
And that she's pretty.

82
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:22,967
- You look good together, Daddy.
- Shh! Look at this kid.

83
00:04:23,067 --> 00:04:24,967
Always telling
the silliest things.

84
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:27,100
Just focus on your dinner.

85
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,033
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,300
King...

87
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:33,800
Miss Agnes already has
a husband.

88
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:35,967
Too bad.

89
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:38,300
Because, Daddy...

90
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:42,133
I think she was the angel
who saved me.

91
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:45,200
I wish she were my mom.

92
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:52,167
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,667
Sure.

94
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:56,333
She's an angel.

95
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:05,833
[FOOD SIZZLING]

96
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:10,667
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:11,933
Angel?

98
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:32,667
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

99
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:55,067
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,767
[CRICKETS CHIRPING
IN THE DISTANCE]

101
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:06,400
I heard you've been trying
to find the kidnapper

102
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:08,533
of Samuel Trinidad's son.

103
00:06:08,667 --> 00:06:10,100
That's true, Detective.

104
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:12,433
But the thing is...

105
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,100
no one seems interested in
pursuing the case anymore.

106
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,500
No follow-up requests
or anything.

107
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,633
So, I decided to do it myself.

108
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,600
I like that.

109
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:23,433
Keep doing what you do.

110
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,433
Actually...

111
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:28,633
that kidnapper really got
my blood boiling.

112
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,767
That bastard managed
to escape from us.

113
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:32,167
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,433
[SCOFFS]

115
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:35,433
Do you have a lead?

116
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:38,100
Not yet.

117
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:54,333
- That's from--
- Retrieved from the location.

118
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,933
Have them open it.

119
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:59,267
You might uncover some
substantial evidence.

120
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:02,133
This will greatly help
with the investigation.

121
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:03,700
You want that promotion, right?

122
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:07,367
If you ever manage
to close this case,

123
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,200
the higher-ups are bound
to notice of you.

124
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:12,200
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:13,700
I won't let you down.

126
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,833
- Good luck.
- Thank you, sir.

127
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,567
[KEYPAD CLICKING]

128
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:30,200
"Hi, Ms. Cecilia Cruz.
Do you remember me?"

129
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:34,367
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

130
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:38,833
"I'm Mike Trinidad's daughter."

131
00:07:49,533 --> 00:07:54,600
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:56,867
Is everything okay?
Any problems?

133
00:07:57,900 --> 00:08:00,033
No, I'm okay.

134
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,167
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

135
00:08:17,267 --> 00:08:19,000
[GLASSES CLINKING]

136
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:25,033
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:08:25,167 --> 00:08:26,067
[GROANS]

138
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:30,533
[PHONE CHIMES]

139
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,433
Give us a moment.

140
00:08:40,267 --> 00:08:41,133
[SNIFFLES]

141
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:44,133
[NUMBER PAD CLICKING]

142
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:51,067
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

143
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,267
Open it.

144
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:09,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:14,600
[LINE RINGING]

146
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,067
[PHONE BUZZING]

147
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:17,900
[CLEARS THROAT]

148
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,100
I just saw your message.

149
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,600
Good.

150
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:25,133
At least now you know
I'm a man of my word.

151
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,267
[SNICKERS]

152
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:27,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

153
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,967
That's funny.

154
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,467
This is way too little.
Where's the rest?

155
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:34,467
[SAMUEL]
That's only 50 million dollars.

156
00:09:34,567 --> 00:09:36,767
Consider that my down payment.

157
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,933
Down payment?
Where's the rest of the money?

158
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:46,133
Come on now.
You'll get the rest soon enough.

159
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,833
Just give me what I want.

160
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,800
You already know what it is.

161
00:09:50,967 --> 00:09:53,633
So, take your time
with my offer.

162
00:09:54,367 --> 00:09:56,000
You sure love making things
hard for everyone.

163
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:57,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,967
Hello?

165
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,467
[LINE DROPPED]

166
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,700
Hello?

167
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:19,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:26,167
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

169
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,400
[JACOB] That little bastard.

170
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:30,833
Unbelievable.

171
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:34,333
Fifty million? Down payment?

172
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:37,967
That's barely a fraction of what
his father stole from us.

173
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:38,867
You know...

174
00:10:38,967 --> 00:10:41,200
He's really testing me.

175
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:45,933
Roldan, let's just do it.

176
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,900
Let's teach Samuel a lesson.

177
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:49,600
You said it yourself.

178
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,267
He's getting on your nerves.

179
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,033
We shouldn't let him
insult us like this.

180
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:58,700
What do you want us to do?
Kill his family?

181
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,000
What if he kills himself?

182
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:01,833
- Come on, Roldan.
- What?

183
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:03,933
Then we won't get
our money back!

184
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,600
Roldan...

185
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:09,200
Do you really think
he'll kill himself?

186
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:13,033
And leave his son and mother
on their own?

187
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,367
[SCOFFS] Roldan...

188
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:19,033
I don't think he'll do that.

189
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:22,467
He's just doing this
to play with us.

190
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:26,433
So, let's put Samuel
in his place.

191
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:28,633
Let's force him
to get our money.

192
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:35,600
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,633
Bro, you can't just pay them
in installments forever.

194
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,733
What's your next step?

195
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,400
I don't have one yet.

196
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:43,767
I'm just buying time.

197
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:48,667
I'm trying to win
Roldan's trust.

198
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,767
I can't do anything
until I win his trust.

199
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:53,733
Plan your next move carefully.

200
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:56,300
Otherwise, you're dead.

201
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,733
I can do this, man.

202
00:11:58,533 --> 00:11:59,633
Alright.

203
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:01,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:12:01,767 --> 00:12:04,900
You can't do this alone.

205
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:06,167
Aside from me and Mael,

206
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,267
You have to have someone
you can trust.

207
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:11,300
Someone who knows the ins
and outs of their operations.

208
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:17,633
Do you feel better now?

209
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:24,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

210
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:42,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:12:42,567 --> 00:12:43,500
What's this about?!

212
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:48,933
Who are you?
What do you want?

213
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,200
[MAN] Drive.
We're going somewhere.

214
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:54,867
What do you want?

215
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,233
[MAN] Just drive, or I'll
blow your brains out!

216
00:12:58,767 --> 00:12:59,800
Go on.

217
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:06,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,067
[MAN] Come on!

219
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,133
[SAMUEL] What's this for?!

220
00:13:13,267 --> 00:13:15,733
- [MAN] Go in!
- [SAMUEL] What's going on?!

221
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,633
[SAMUEL]
Where are you taking me?!

222
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:19,067
[MAN] Sit!

223
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,567
[HUFFS]

224
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:28,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:42,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS]

226
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:00,467
[ROLDAN SPEAKING IN
DISTORTED VOICE] Well, Trinidad?

227
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,433
You still tough?

228
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:11,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:14:26,067 --> 00:14:29,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,267
Can you still handle it?

231
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:41,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:14:51,433 --> 00:14:52,433
What's going on?

233
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,800
What do you want from me?

234
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:56,333
[BANGING ON GLASS] Huh?!

235
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,767
What do you want from me?!

236
00:14:58,867 --> 00:14:59,800
[BANGING ON GLASS]

237
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:04,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:06,967
You know what I need
from you, right?

239
00:15:07,067 --> 00:15:14,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,833
[DOOR OPENS]

241
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,933
[DOOR CLOSES]

242
00:15:26,533 --> 00:15:32,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:34,467
I already told you, remember?

244
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:39,867
If you do this again,
I'll kill myself!

245
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,233
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

246
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,967
Oh, so you're
challenging me now, huh?

247
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:49,067
Go on then, kill yourself.

248
00:15:50,033 --> 00:15:52,000
- Sit down!
- [BREATHES HEAVILY]

249
00:15:54,867 --> 00:15:56,367
Prove to me...

250
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,333
...you're not just all talk.

251
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:02,533
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

252
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:09,700
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:10,900
[GUN THUDS]

254
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:22,567
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:36,233
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,400
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

257
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,367
I already have you
in my grip, right?

258
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:42,100
I already kidnapped you.

259
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:44,800
[ROLDAN IN ALTERED VOICE]
Go on, kill yourself!

260
00:16:44,967 --> 00:16:52,033
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

261
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,733
Are you just all talk?

262
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:04,767
Go on, kill yourself!

263
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:11,933
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:18,133
Roldan, he won't do it.

265
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:19,800
He's just messing with us.

266
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:26,967
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:48,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

268
00:18:04,033 --> 00:18:11,000
